>','P52BW13: Fading','','publish','open','open','','p52bw13-fading','','','2013-04-21 12:23:13','2013-04-21 18:23:13','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1006',0,'post','',0),(1008,1,'2013-04-23 15:53:36','2013-04-23 21:53:36','I recently shared a picture on Facebook of Katie pointing to this mac, which my Dad replied to and indicated his shock that this was now in a museum. Since its nearly 30 years old, I figured a museum sounded like a pretty good spot for it, and my mom pointed out that based on that criteria I now qualify to be in a museum too.\n\nI don\'t know about everyone else, but I really love the way this came out with the post processing. It really feels like something you\'d see in the 80s.\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/edJfDJ\n\n<img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8521/8676679924_1081e65fb4_b.jpg\" />','This is in a museum?','','publish','open','open','','this-is-in-a-museum','','','2013-04-23 15:53:36','2013-04-23 21:53:36','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1008',0,'post','',0),(1010,1,'2013-04-25 21:53:14','2013-04-26 03:53:14','I processed this image three times before I liked this version of it. From the other morning on Slacker Hill. I haven\'t been able to get out and shoot much the last couple of weeks so just working through the back catalog. Hopefully I\'ll get some time to shoot this weekend.\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/eeaTQH\n\n<img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8394/8681682829_45f214659c_b.jpg\" />','Third time&#039;s a charm','','publish','open','open','','third-times-a-charm','','','2013-04-25 21:53:14','2013-04-26 03:53:14','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1010',0,'post','',0),(1015,1,'2013-04-26 22:53:49','2013-04-27 04:53:49','<div><img src=\'http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8402/8684288841_a5771fe823_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>I\'ve been trying to get a bit more into street photography, but I\'m working up my nerve to capture people as I see them with them possibly knowing I\'m photographing them, so instead I\'m easing into it by starting with asleep people.  On the BART on the way home, I thought these two people\'s heads made for a nice line.  Shot with my iPhone 4S and edited with Snapseed.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/eepfvX</div></div>','You Snooze You Lose','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-04-26 22:53:49','2013-04-27 04:53:49','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1015',0,'post','',0),(1017,1,'2013-04-27 22:08:28','2013-04-28 04:08:28','From a few weeks ago. I don\'t know if the odds of an overcast morning are greater on Sunday, but they seem like they are sometimes. I\'ll be back out tomorrow morning, hoping for low fog instead of low clouds.\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/eeKcQ1\n\n<img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8399/8688182036_46ff8b7852_b.jpg\" />','An Overcast Morning','','publish','open','open','','an-overcast-morning','','','2013-04-27 22:08:28','2013-04-28 04:08:28','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1017',0,'post','',0),(1019,1,'2013-04-29 21:38:38','2013-04-30 03:38:38','From New Years Day. I\'m going out to Drink and Click tomorrow so maybe I\'ll shoot something new to post, but in the mean time still posting from my backlog. I shot and processed this many months ago, but just never made it to the top of my list to post :).\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/efg3nZ\n\n<img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8123/8694003611_ac4855f3fa_b.jpg\" />','A City Silhouette','','publish','open','open','','a-city-silhouette','','','2013-04-29 21:38:38','2013-04-30 03:38:38','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1019',0,'post','',0),(1021,1,'2013-05-01 22:53:37','2013-05-02 04:53:37','From last night\'s Drink &amp; Click at the Palace of Fine Arts. Thanks to Tony for organizing yet again, it was a lot of fun, and we actually took photos this time!\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/efU9od\n\n<img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8255/8701242952_b171d7d049_b.jpg\" />','Photographers Palace','','publish','open','open','','photographers-palace','','','2013-05-01 22:53:37','2013-05-02 04:53:37','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1021',0,'post','',0),(1023,1,'2013-05-03 12:23:15','2013-05-03 18:23:15','I loved the arc of light jutting out from behind this building that looks like its framing the Chrysler building. Having Grand Central in the foreground isn\'t bad either .\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/egbFMg\n\n<img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8115/8704470365_4bb2c5b7eb_b.jpg\" />','P52BW13: Night Lights','','publish','open','open','','p52bw13-night-lights','','','2013-05-03 12:23:15','2013-05-03 18:23:15','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1023',0,'post','',0),(1025,1,'2013-05-04 19:23:36','2013-05-05 01:23:36','Clouds or not, I love a rich blue sky. From Palace of Fine Arts at last week\'s Drink &amp; Click.\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/egAWN7\n\n<img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8540/8709203562_61119ea3c4_b.jpg\" />','I love a rich blue sky','','publish','open','open','','i-love-a-rich-blue-sky','','','2013-05-04 19:23:36','2013-05-05 01:23:36','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1025',0,'post','',0),(1027,1,'2013-05-05 18:53:38','2013-05-06 00:53:38','In the photography world, these are occurences of the sun breaking through the clouds are called several things, but usually I hear them referred to as \"God Rays\". This is the first time I\'ve had the opportunity to photograph the phenomenon, but it was quite spectacular. They only last a minute in one spot usually before they\'re gone, so I\'m fortunate to have captured this one right over Alcatraz.\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/egUBZj\n\n<img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8403/8712652312_070bcfe5cd_b.jpg\" />','And The Heavens Parted','','publish','open','open','','and-the-heavens-parted','','','2013-05-05 18:53:38','2013-05-06 00:53:38','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1027',0,'post','',0),(1029,1,'2013-05-06 22:53:34','2013-05-07 04:53:34','I don\'t know if this pixie dust will allow you to take flight, but I like to think it would.\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/ehgVWQ\n\n<img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7460/8716810072_f1f70eafd0_b.jpg\" />','Pixie Dust','','publish','open','open','','pixie-dust','','','2013-05-06 22:53:34','2013-05-07 04:53:34','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1029',0,'post','',0),(1038,1,'2013-05-07 16:53:24','2013-05-07 22:53:24','From Grand Central Terminal in New York City. I was there last week for one night only but I did get a chance to go shoot here. It\'s really a great place to shoot. So much activity. Half the people are rushing along trying to get to their train and the other half are taking pictures of themselves.\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/ehob9v\n\n<img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7453/8718028517_26a7d9a46a_b.jpg\" />','100','','publish','open','open','','100','','','2013-05-07 16:53:24','2013-05-07 22:53:24','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1038',0,'post','',0),(1040,1,'2013-05-09 17:23:55','2013-05-09 23:23:55','From last night at Rodeo Beach. I don\'t normally get to pick when I shoot based on weather, I generally go based on a schedule of days that work for me and my family so therefore I have to make do with what weather I find. In this case, it was completley overcast, so had to work with that. I quite like the result. I plan to continue working more on B&amp;W Long Exposure stuff as it always turns out so well.\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/ehZ48E\n\n<img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7385/8724833840_985441bf8f_b.jpg\" />','Stacks','','publish','open','open','','stacks','','','2013-05-09 17:23:55','2013-05-09 23:23:55','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1040',0,'post','',0),(1042,1,'2013-05-10 21:23:32','2013-05-11 03:23:32','Looks like there was some decent fog over the bridge tonight. I\'ll be up tomorrow morning to try to catch it again. #fogchasing\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/eifNHS\n\n<img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7368/8727907156_8560d546ae_b.jpg\" />','Here&#039;s hoping for fog','','publish','open','open','','heres-hoping-for-fog','','','2013-05-10 21:23:32','2013-05-11 03:23:32','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1042',0,'post','',0),(1048,1,'2013-05-12 12:23:41','2013-05-12 18:23:41','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7282/8732794950_87fed8f46d_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div><br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/eiFRGb</div></div>','I think I&#039;m going to like Hipstamatic. For the iPhone post processing everything in Snapseed seems like a burden. Better to pick it all up front and live with it.','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-05-12 12:23:41','2013-05-12 18:23:41','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1048',0,'post','',0),(1050,1,'2013-05-13 13:38:55','2013-05-13 19:38:55','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7298/8736469290_5d80f59255.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div><br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/ej1FWS</div></div>','It has reached that point in the all day meeting.','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-05-13 13:38:55','2013-05-13 19:38:55','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1050',0,'post','',0),(1052,1,'2013-05-13 23:32:19','2013-05-14 05:32:19','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7285/8737781812_cece4fbba1.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div><br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/ej8q7y</div></div>','There&#039;s just something I live about long hotel hallways. They&#039;re creepy.','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-05-13 23:32:19','2013-05-14 05:32:19','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1052',0,'post','',0),(1054,1,'2013-05-14 18:23:36','2013-05-15 00:23:36','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7281/8740139402_9fba08c8ec.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div><br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/ejkuWE</div></div>','The Philly Ritz','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-05-14 18:23:36','2013-05-15 00:23:36','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1054',0,'post','',0),(1056,1,'2013-05-15 17:53:19','2013-05-15 23:53:19','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7282/8741939441_c684d943f8.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div><br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/ejuJ2P</div></div>','Protests at the White House.','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-05-15 17:53:19','2013-05-15 23:53:19','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1056',0,'post','',0),(1058,1,'2013-05-19 12:38:28','2013-05-19 18:38:28','From the reflecting pool in Washington, DC. What I learned from using my D3100 as a backup while my D600 was out: Hot Pixels are a massive issue on the D3100, I need to get my sensor cleaned on this body as well, and color representation on the D3100 is poor compared to the D600. Can\'t wait to get the D600 back from Nikon.\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/ekDGcS\n\n<img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2864/8755005800_cdb6e7e9e5_b.jpg\" />','Reflecting','','publish','open','open','','reflecting','','','2013-05-19 12:38:28','2013-05-19 18:38:28','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1058',0,'post','',0),(1062,1,'2013-05-24 22:08:29','2013-05-25 04:08:29','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7281/8821234374_e0893c7486_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>The bridge is a frequent subject, but this is a different view at least for me.  I\'ve been working on long exposure B&amp;W photography.  I frequently get stuck with overcast weather when I go out to shoot, but this day it was not only overcast but also quickly moving clouds which really makes for the perfect weather for long exposure.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/erv8DQ</div></div>','A different view','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-05-24 22:08:29','2013-05-25 04:08:29','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1062',0,'post','',0),(1064,1,'2013-05-27 21:23:55','2013-05-28 03:23:55','<div><img src=\'http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2875/8862612132_33d2253f5c_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>This duck stayed still for 252 seconds during this long exposure.  Not only was it frigid, but it was also incredibly windy.  He stayed there like a champ though.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/evacPs</div></div>','Stay Still Little Duck','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-05-27 21:23:55','2013-05-28 03:23:55','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1064',0,'post','',0),(1066,1,'2013-05-30 18:23:35','2013-05-31 00:23:35','<div><img src=\'http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5446/8896617464_89a9198b71_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>I moved to Oakland over the weekend to my new house where I hope to stay for the next 10 years at least.  One nice feature of the new house is that it\'s literally 5 minutes from Grizzly Peak Blvd / Skyline Blvd in Oakland giving me fantastic views of the city like this.  I just received my D600 back from Nikon with a replaced shutter mechanism to (hopefully) solve the sensor dust issue.  So far so good, no sensor spots on these shots, but we\'ll know more in a few thousand exposures.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/eyauqh</div></div>','Just up the hill','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-05-30 18:23:35','2013-05-31 00:23:35','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1066',0,'post','',0),(1068,1,'2013-06-04 00:39:00','2013-06-04 06:39:00','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7422/8944985673_15408075a5_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>This duck stayed still for 252 seconds during this long exposure.  Not only was it frigid, but it was also incredibly windy.  He stayed there like a champ though.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/eCroAV</div></div>','Stay Still Little Duck','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-06-04 00:39:00','2013-06-04 06:39:00','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1068',0,'post','',0),(1070,1,'2013-06-04 00:39:02','2013-06-04 06:39:02','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3739/8945611486_c0f6e76645_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>First image I\'m posting from #MendoPixelsTrip2013 with friends.  This is after sunrise with a beautiful golden light on the Point Cabrillo Lighthouse in Mendocino, CA.gzg<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/eCuACN</div></div>','Golden Lighthouse','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-06-04 00:39:02','2013-06-04 06:39:02','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1070',0,'post','',0),(1072,1,'2013-06-06 20:53:15','2013-06-07 02:53:15','<div><img src=\'http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5444/8974756386_3d14f37ebd_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>Low tide didn\'t give us the best perspective, so I decided to try a wider one at Bowling Ball Beach.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/eF4Yp5</div></div>','Bowling Ball Landscape','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-06-06 20:53:15','2013-06-07 02:53:15','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1072',0,'post','',0),(1074,1,'2013-06-07 21:09:08','2013-06-08 03:09:08','<div><img src=\'http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2884/8982388165_69cb33f8db_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>From the last Drink &amp; Click.  While everyone was at the Palace of Fine Arts, I ran to catch the sunset over the Golden Gate which was quite special that evening.  This is one of my favorite Golden Images I\'ve taken.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/eFK64t</div></div>','Fire Consumes Bridge','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-06-07 21:09:08','2013-06-08 03:09:08','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1074',0,'post','',0),(1076,1,'2013-06-11 21:08:42','2013-06-12 03:08:42','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3749/9022627658_5c8dfae320_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>I\'m home sick right now.  I\'ve been laid up for 4 days with no end in sight.  To remedy this, I\'m posting a beautiful sunrise from my recent trip to the Northern California coastline near Fort Bragg.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/eKijRQ</div></div>','Something Pretty','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-06-11 21:08:42','2013-06-12 03:08:42','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1076',0,'post','',0),(1078,1,'2013-06-20 23:23:21','2013-06-21 05:23:21','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7401/9096741495_20a994fa2a_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>Monuments are symbols of power, and um, yeah, other things that make men feel powerful.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/eRRbjB</div></div>','Phallic Reflections','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-06-20 23:23:21','2013-06-21 05:23:21','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1078',0,'post','',0),(1080,1,'2013-06-25 20:23:35','2013-06-26 02:23:35','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7292/9138437949_96b4856e59_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>The Bay Bridge from the Embarcadero.  This was my first time out looking at the new Bay Lights.  Framed right, the glow from Oakland is very pretty.  Makes for a very interesting gradiant from the blue hour sky to the orange harbor lights.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/eVwTdZ</div></div>','Oakland Glow','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-06-25 20:23:35','2013-06-26 02:23:35','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1080',0,'post','',0),(1082,1,'2013-07-05 14:38:35','2013-07-05 20:38:35','<div><img src=\'http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2879/9219090734_8c7b3a3ff0.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div><br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/f3Efuf</div></div>','The Brunswick 2000. State of the art bowling computer.','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-07-05 14:38:35','2013-07-05 20:38:35','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1082',0,'post','',0),(1084,1,'2013-07-08 23:23:18','2013-07-09 05:23:18','<div><img src=\'http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5337/9243609697_58841d3bf7_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>From Bowling Ball Beach.  I look forward to visiting here when we have a bit more time and better conditions, but still had a fantastic time with friends.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/f5PV7Z</div></div>','Beach Balls','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-07-08 23:23:18','2013-07-09 05:23:18','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1084',0,'post','',0),(1086,1,'2013-07-10 21:38:27','2013-07-11 03:38:27','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3696/9257521681_3e31d6ae05_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>When I\'m up in the hills behind my house, often the haze prevents taking good photos of the city.  However, I\'m almost always happy with my view of Mt. Tam and Marin County.  Processed in Color Efex Pro 4.  With +Maximillian Laue.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/f74dEM</div></div>','Sunset behind Tam','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-07-10 21:38:27','2013-07-11 03:38:27','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1086',0,'post','',0),(1088,1,'2013-07-11 22:53:28','2013-07-12 04:53:28','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7412/9267811568_e638803283_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>Some day I\'ll post the original version which has a gaggle of photographers that I cleverly edited out of the photo.  As my wife pointed out, this looks like a Sandals advertisement.  If so, it\'d be a modern one, with one person drinking a beer and the other playing on their cell phone.  What a nice day at the beach.  #mendopixelstrip2013<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/f7XXuC</div></div>','Who knew there was a Sandals in Mendocino?','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-07-11 22:53:28','2013-07-12 04:53:28','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1088',0,'post','',0),(1090,1,'2013-07-12 21:38:26','2013-07-13 03:38:26','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7285/9271632685_059c835756_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>Sometimes you\'re just so excited about a photo you can\'t wait to publish it.  I feel this way about this one.  I love taking photos of my dog.  Sometimes she\'s just really accommodating of my picture taking.  Other times, she\'s impossible, but last night she was content to lay on the floor and let me continually blind her with my strobe.  Seventy captures later, there\'s a great keeper.  I think it\'s my best Dog Portrait to date.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/f8ixnX</div></div>','Dog Portraiture','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-07-12 21:38:26','2013-07-13 03:38:26','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1090',0,'post','',0),(1092,1,'2013-07-15 21:23:59','2013-07-16 03:23:59','<div><img src=\'http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5325/9295625661_9cae107c6b_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>The summer fog isn\'t interesting.  It\'s generally high fog, blocks the good views of the Bay, keeps the city and the East Bay shrouded in overcast skies, and in general is just weather I can\'t say I\'m fond of.  Bring on Fall!  In the mean time, I guess I can take advantage of the situation a bit and get a shot of the Bay Bridge and the city shrouded in High Fog.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/faqvDX</div></div>','Ready for Fall','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-07-15 21:23:59','2013-07-16 03:23:59','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1092',0,'post','',0),(1094,1,'2013-07-18 22:08:23','2013-07-19 04:08:23','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3684/9316682739_2b05a7eb08_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>Another from the other night at the Bay Bridge.  I actually edited this one first, because I hadn\'t already captured this perspective in a photo I\'ve shared.  I wish tail lights were brighter; they\'d make for better streaks.d<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fchrc2</div></div>','More Bridge Less City','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-07-18 22:08:23','2013-07-19 04:08:23','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1094',0,'post','',0),(1096,1,'2013-07-20 20:08:38','2013-07-21 02:08:38','<div><img src=\'http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2813/9329403557_7653ff22fb_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>I seem to have fortunate timing.  I emailed Camera West yesterday looking for an X100S right after they had taken one in as a return.  I drove up to Walnut Creek this morning, picked it up, and spent the afternoon out at the park with Katie playing around with it.  Still a lot to learn about using this particular camera.  So far it\'s small, light, but behaves in the way I\'d expect my SLR to behave.  With an APS-C sized sensor and a f/2 lens, I can get good subject isolation and fast shutter speeds, although given the way the camera autofocuses I wouldn\'t expect much action photography with it.  Anyways, I\'m really really happy so far.  I\'m looking forward to my New Orleans trip where it\'ll really get a workout.  #x100s<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fdpCDt</div></div>','New Camera &amp; A Day @ The Park','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-07-20 20:08:38','2013-07-21 02:08:38','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1096',0,'post','',0),(1098,1,'2013-07-23 21:53:35','2013-07-24 03:53:35','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7415/9353955271_8aa23bc51e_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>The X100S is small enough to take with me when I ride the BART.  2nd St. makes for occasionally interesting subjects.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/ffzt1T</div></div>','Two Minis','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-07-23 21:53:35','2013-07-24 03:53:35','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1098',0,'post','',0),(1100,1,'2013-07-28 22:08:21','2013-07-29 04:08:21','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3795/9390952956_892c79535d_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>Friday nights are family night.  We play a board game and then watch a movie.  Katie made a sign which says &quot;no cameras&quot; and &quot;no cell phones.&quot;  I honor the no cell phone rule as much as possible, but the no camera rule is impossible especially since I just got this #x100s.  This is Straight Out of the Camera (#SOOC in photographer-speak).  It\'s a raw developed as B&amp;W with a Red Filter.  I\'m continually more impressed with this camera the more i use it.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fiR691</div></div>','Family Night','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-07-28 22:08:21','2013-07-29 04:08:21','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1100',0,'post','',0),(1102,1,'2013-08-03 19:09:37','2013-08-04 01:09:37','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3732/9433204052_f6c3308685_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>This is from SEATAC.  I was up in Seattle for the day visiting coworkers at our office in Seattle.  Unfortunately flying into San Francisco this time of the year is always troublesome due to fog, and even worse by the end of the day.  By the time I was scheduled to leave around 7, they were already 3 hours behind.  That did give me a specific advantage in the fact that I was able to stay for a killer sunset.  The sky behind the mountains looked like it was on fire.  I had my handy Fuji #X100S which has quickly become my favorite camera due to its portability.  That plus my handy Slik tabletop tripod and I was able to capture a number of great shots out the windows of the airport.  I wish I had a polarizer to try to minimize the glare from the windows, which ruined most of my shots, but this shot was at least fairly minimal in terms of glare.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fnzCVb</div></div>','Delayed','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-08-03 19:09:37','2013-08-04 01:09:37','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1102',0,'post','',0),(1104,1,'2013-08-04 16:08:20','2013-08-04 22:08:20','<div><img src=\'http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2878/9440115298_7d7712d8d6_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>This photo is the exact reason I bought the Fuji #X100S.  Taken a f/2 at 1/1000sec this is basically straight out of the camera.  The X100S has a remarkable flash sync speed up to 1/2000sec.  Explaining why this is important is complicated, and others do a better job, but my very expensive SLR can only do 1/200 sec which means I cannot use the flash with a wide open shutter like this and get this kind of photo.  The end result, as you can see, is very impressive.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/foc4oA</div></div>','Overpowering the Sun','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-08-04 16:08:20','2013-08-04 22:08:20','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1104',0,'post','',0),(1106,1,'2013-08-08 22:53:39','2013-08-09 04:53:39','<div><img src=\'http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5533/9470884676_59ffddf131_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>I don\'t know in particular why I liked this photo so well, but these workers at Cafe Du Monde in New Orleans captured my attention.  Obviously, something else had captured their attention.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fqUL47</div></div>','Something over there','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-08-08 22:53:39','2013-08-09 04:53:39','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1106',0,'post','',0),(1108,1,'2013-08-09 18:53:48','2013-08-10 00:53:48','<div><img src=\'http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5523/9476561216_78ca47b189_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>Melanie and I shopping on Bourbon Street.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/frpRuu</div></div>','Beauty in Reflection','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-08-09 18:53:48','2013-08-10 00:53:48','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1108',0,'post','',0),(1110,1,'2013-08-10 18:23:40','2013-08-11 00:23:40','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7371/9480463361_cc684010ff_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>Spent some time in St. Louis Cathedral in Jackson Square in New Orleans.  I love the votives they light in cathedrals.  So pretty.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/frKRsR</div></div>','Cathedral Candles','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-08-10 18:23:40','2013-08-11 00:23:40','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1110',0,'post','',0),(1112,1,'2013-08-11 19:53:20','2013-08-12 01:53:20','<div><img src=\'http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5509/9491903404_a3a3d3d346_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>My friends back home in Arkansas will recognize this location.  I\'m sure the rest of you wont.  This is a local landmark outside Lavaca, Arkansas at the intersection of highways 22 and 96, essentially in the middle of nowhere.  This farmer painted this grain tower as a Budweiser Can back in 1975.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fsLubY</div></div>','Budweiser Can Sunset','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-08-11 19:53:20','2013-08-12 01:53:20','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1112',0,'post','',0),(1114,1,'2013-08-16 19:38:46','2013-08-17 01:38:46','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3826/9525297623_514155e35c_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>View of Hong Kong from Victoria Peak.  Very sincere thanks to Andy Ho and others who brought me up here to take pictures.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fvHD8n</div></div>','Victoria Harbor Pano','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-08-16 19:38:46','2013-08-17 01:38:46','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1114',0,'post','',0),(1116,1,'2013-08-19 08:23:23','2013-08-19 14:23:23','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3820/9547668480_b105210f86_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>From Sydney Harbor in Australia.  These two ladies were sitting calmly watching the sun go down as I passed them by.  Sometimes I\'m envious of the people who spend the time merely watching the scenes I am intensely trying to capture with my camera.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fxGicN</div></div>','Peaceful Southern Sunset','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-08-19 08:23:23','2013-08-19 14:23:23','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1116',0,'post','',0),(1118,1,'2013-08-20 21:23:41','2013-08-21 03:23:41','<div><img src=\'http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5468/9560807378_a2c24a857d_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>From Fort Smith, Arkansas.  Since I had some spare time on Sunday night, and I love photographing bridges, I thought it would be good to get a sunset treatment of the Garrison Ave Bridge in my hometown.  The Golden Gate it\'s not, but hey its home.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fyRCWw</div></div>','Garrison Avenue Bridge Sunset','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-08-20 21:23:41','2013-08-21 03:23:41','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1118',0,'post','',0),(1120,1,'2013-08-22 18:24:00','2013-08-23 00:24:00','<div><img src=\'http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5502/9574046636_8b664380db_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>Seen on the streets of Hong Kong.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fA2uvA</div></div>','Sleek','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-08-22 18:24:00','2013-08-23 00:24:00','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1120',0,'post','',0),(1122,1,'2013-08-24 20:23:27','2013-08-25 02:23:27','<div><img src=\'http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2858/9588069732_1e6c76c1e7_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>Sitting at Narita at Starbucks waiting on my flight.  It\'s been a wonderful time here in Japan, but I\'m ready to come home.  From Shibuya Crossing in the rain.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fBgn67</div></div>','Sayonara','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-08-24 20:23:27','2013-08-25 02:23:27','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1122',0,'post','',0),(1124,1,'2013-08-28 22:08:35','2013-08-29 04:08:35','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7394/9620567384_2d16f176af_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>From right outside St. Louis Cemetary #1 in New Orleans.  I heard, assuming its true, that they do not use horses to pull carriages in New Orleans by city ordinance, only mules, because mules do better with the heat and workload.  This &quot;workhorse&quot; stayed and posed for me while I got this picture of him.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fE8Vvs</div></div>','Work &quot;horse&quot;','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-08-28 22:08:35','2013-08-29 04:08:35','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1124',0,'post','',0),(1126,1,'2013-08-29 21:38:24','2013-08-30 03:38:24','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3831/9624232157_2b55b6e4ed_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>From Berkeley Pier.  I\'ve read the old pier extended a mile and a half into the bay, but the current one only goes about a half a mile.  You can see the remains of the old pier through the gap in the slats at the end of the current pier, which makes for a really nice foreground for a sunset.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fEsGVc</div></div>','Pier in the Bay','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-08-29 21:38:24','2013-08-30 03:38:24','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1126',0,'post','',0),(1128,1,'2013-08-30 17:53:34','2013-08-30 23:53:34','<div><img src=\'http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2809/9630366621_e8ee7ece9b_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>From Mrs. Macquarie\'s Chair in Sydney, Australia.  Beautiful clear evening a week and a half ago.  Sydney is one of the most beautiful harbors I\'ve seen.  It was a pleasure to photograph.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fF19tP</div></div>','Crystal Clear Sydney Skyline Pano','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-08-30 17:53:34','2013-08-30 23:53:34','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1128',0,'post','',0),(1130,1,'2013-08-31 21:23:41','2013-09-01 03:23:41','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3674/9639361653_d554c9ea9a_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>I wish she was this calm allg the time.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fFNfoz</div></div>','Wistful','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-08-31 21:23:41','2013-09-01 03:23:41','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1130',0,'post','',0),(1132,1,'2013-09-02 21:08:36','2013-09-03 03:08:36','<div><img src=\'http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5441/9658272853_b5ae986453_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>From abandoned church facade in downtown Fort Smith, Arkansas around 5th or 6th street.  This facade was just sitting there, with no church behind it.  The window looks out to another house which is either abandoned or in severe disrepair.  Sad that nobody is maintaining these old properties anymore right in the heart of the city.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fHtb2K</div></div>','Window to Nowhere','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-09-02 21:08:36','2013-09-03 03:08:36','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1132',0,'post','',0),(1134,1,'2013-09-07 22:08:15','2013-09-08 04:08:15','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3708/9695693379_ab92a7b079_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>From my best friend Brent\'s place in Charleston, Arkansas.  Good times with friends.  Wish I could spend more time back home, but the pictures at least help keep the memories alive.  #x100s<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fLLXRe</div></div>','Garage Poolhall','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-09-07 22:08:15','2013-09-08 04:08:15','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1134',0,'post','',0),(1136,1,'2013-09-08 23:38:31','2013-09-09 05:38:31','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7365/9708328390_7e8e2d0bf0_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>Trains are enamouring.  Its hard to imagine a time when travel was slower, but I think compared to today it might have been more interesting, and more exciting.  Given no Internet, no Television, every new place was a surprise.  This is from downtown Fort Smith, Arkansas, where they keep a few decaying trains on display that turned out quite pretty during sunset.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fMTHNf</div></div>','We used to travel in style','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2013-09-08 23:38:31','2013-09-09 05:38:31','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1136',0,'post','',0),(1138,1,'2013-09-09 22:38:43','2013-09-10 04:38:43','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2805/9712548315_aca4ccee74_b.jpg\" />\n<div>I have many pictures of the inside of this cathedral I\'ve yet to publish. I think I could spend some time every place I\'m at looking at old churches. They just don\'t build them like that anymore.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fNgmez\n\n</div>\n</div>','St. Louis Cathedral','','publish','closed','open','','st-louis-cathedral','','','2013-09-09 22:38:43','2013-09-10 04:38:43','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1138',0,'post','',0),(1140,1,'2013-09-10 21:08:16','2013-09-11 03:08:16','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5519/9722615328_413a7a4ac1_b.jpg\" />\n<div>Everyone\'s posting about the new span, but it wasn\'t long ago that the Bay Lights were the new hotness. From March shortly after the new lights were lit.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fP9WNL\n\n</div>\n</div>','Show Me Your Lights','','publish','closed','open','','show-me-your-lights','','','2013-09-10 21:08:16','2013-09-11 03:08:16','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1140',0,'post','',0),(1142,1,'2013-09-11 22:09:04','2013-09-12 04:09:04','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2875/9729849616_d7c4d2790d_b.jpg\" />\n<div>Working through it slowly but surely. From January. This was the most brilliant sunset I\'ve ever seen, although we\'ve had some good ones the past month that I wasn\'t able to get out and photograph.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fPN2iS\n\n</div>\n</div>','Back Catalog','','publish','closed','open','','back-catalog','','','2013-09-11 22:09:04','2013-09-12 04:09:04','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1142',0,'post','',0),(1144,1,'2013-09-12 22:11:35','2013-09-13 04:11:35','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5538/9733199427_6d1be4fea4_b.jpg\" />\n<div>I distinctly remember this morning. I was on Treasure Island, hoping to catch the moonrise, photographing furiously around 3:30 AM when I hear my name shouted at me from behind. Scared the living shit out of me. Leave it to Max to see me way out in the underbrush taking pictures while he was walking by. I wasn\'t expecting to see anyone that morning, so obviously was quite shocked to see him.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fQ6c6e\n\n</div>\n</div>','Moonrise Trail','','publish','closed','open','','moonrise-trail','','','2013-09-12 22:11:35','2013-09-13 04:11:35','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1144',0,'post','',0),(1146,1,'2013-09-13 23:41:45','2013-09-14 05:41:45','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7444/9737686655_605106b3b4_b.jpg\" />\n<div>\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fQubZe\n\n</div>\n</div>','Beauty','','publish','closed','open','','beauty','','','2013-09-13 23:41:45','2013-09-14 05:41:45','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1146',0,'post','',0),(1148,1,'2013-09-15 19:47:57','2013-09-16 01:47:57','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7383/9766900516_8573732e99_b.jpg\" />\n<div>I love the reflections of the bridge on the water. From the wayback file, December of last year. I need to go back to Fort Baker again, it\'s been a while.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fT4Vfu\n\n</div>\n</div>','Red Sea','','publish','closed','open','','red-sea','','','2013-09-15 19:47:57','2013-09-16 01:47:57','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1148',0,'post','',0),(1150,1,'2013-09-19 21:36:25','2013-09-20 03:36:25','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3700/9829894923_fa1fc6fe57_b.jpg\" />\n<div>From Berkeley Pier. Even in its current incarnation, it\'s a very long pier. Makes for a cool forground as it mirrors the horizon and provides a nice leading line to the barely visible Golden Gate Bridge in the distance. This was a great sunset. Katie and I had a blast here. HDR handheld with my #x100s.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/fYCMhX\n\n</div>\n</div>','A Line in the Sea','','publish','closed','open','','a-line-in-the-sea','','','2013-09-19 21:36:25','2013-09-20 03:36:25','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1150',0,'post','',0),(1152,1,'2013-09-22 20:23:29','2013-09-23 02:23:29','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3809/9888096146_efd01b79ca_b.jpg\" />\n<div>From the Walnut Festival in Walnut Creek, CA. I am very fond of the Walnut Festival, not because its especially great, but it was the first real outing we had as a family after coming to California last year. Its a harbinger of fall, and hopefully much better weather for photography.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/g4M5uj\n\n</div>\n</div>','Flower Wheel','','publish','closed','open','','flower-wheel','','','2013-09-22 20:23:29','2013-09-23 02:23:29','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1152',0,'post','',0),(1154,1,'2013-09-23 21:35:43','2013-09-24 03:35:43','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3710/9909150395_bace169140_b.jpg\" />\n<div>Even photographers sometimes just stop to take it all in.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/g6CZbB\n\n</div>\n</div>','Stop and Stare','','publish','closed','open','','stop-and-stare','','','2013-09-23 21:35:43','2013-09-24 03:35:43','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1154',0,'post','',0),(1156,1,'2013-09-25 22:47:48','2013-09-26 04:47:48','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7441/9944923794_079bda6197_b.jpg\" />\n<div>#wordlessonwednesdayvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/g9Nknm\n\n</div>\n</div>','Serenity','','publish','closed','open','','serenity','','','2013-09-25 22:47:48','2013-09-26 04:47:48','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1156',0,'post','',0),(1158,1,'2013-09-26 21:17:20','2013-09-27 03:17:20','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5539/9960004775_54dd94a1cc_b.jpg\" />\n<div>Just a regular day at home.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/gb8Cqg\n\n</div>\n</div>','Getting Ready','','publish','closed','open','','getting-ready','','','2013-09-26 21:17:20','2013-09-27 03:17:20','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1158',0,'post','',0),(1160,1,'2013-10-05 15:53:25','2013-10-05 21:53:25','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2856/10106530514_5e978f6e36_b.jpg\" />\n<div>I got lucky and had a friend in Vegas with a suite view (pun intended). From the Cosmopolitan in Las Vegas.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/gp5Bq7\n\n</div>\n</div>','Pie Bob&#039;s Balcony','','publish','closed','open','','pie-bobs-balcony','','','2013-10-05 15:53:25','2013-10-05 21:53:25','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1160',0,'post','',0),(1162,1,'2013-10-14 21:53:54','2013-10-15 03:53:54','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3802/10283904855_0f87274b11_b.jpg\" />\n<div>I was back in Sydney last week. This sunset was a bit more spectacular than the last one I witnessed from this location. Alas they had the area gated off to get out to where the rocks are, so the foreground is limited to some still water from the long exposure.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/gEKGCp\n\n</div>\n</div>','Sydney Once Again','','publish','closed','open','','sydney-once-again','','','2013-10-14 21:53:54','2013-10-15 03:53:54','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1162',0,'post','',0),(1164,1,'2013-10-15 20:59:53','2013-10-16 02:59:53','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2853/10302956124_535733f8a2_b.jpg\" />\n<div>New Orleans was such an awesome place to photograph. I should spend more time doing street photography, its quite enjoyable. This is from the park right off the river in the French Quarter.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/gGrkUy\n\n</div>\n</div>','Meanwhile, on the other side of the tracks...','','publish','closed','open','','meanwhile-on-the-other-side-of-the-tracks','','','2013-10-15 20:59:53','2013-10-16 02:59:53','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1164',0,'post','',0),(1166,1,'2013-10-16 22:29:22','2013-10-17 04:29:22','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7444/10322524513_08fec5e48e_b.jpg\" />\n<div>#wordlessonwednesdayvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/gJaCUz\n\n</div>\n</div>','The Trip Before','','publish','closed','open','','the-trip-before','','','2013-10-16 22:29:22','2013-10-17 04:29:22','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1166',0,'post','',0),(1168,1,'2013-10-17 20:23:30','2013-10-18 02:23:30','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7328/10338251516_e380c243a0.jpg\" />\n<div>\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/gKyeZN\n\n</div>\n</div>','View from 1 Market this afternoon.','','publish','closed','open','','view-from-1-market-this-afternoon','','','2013-10-17 20:23:30','2013-10-18 02:23:30','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1168',0,'post','',0),(1170,1,'2013-10-17 22:11:30','2013-10-18 04:11:30','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3828/10339466346_d7c21bfd8f_b.jpg\" />\n<div>Yesterday evening was shaping up to be a fantastic sunset, but when I got to Fort Baker, I didn\'t have the view I was looking for. I headed back towards the bridge to go to Baker Beach, but there was a reck, I lost 20 minutes waiting to get on the bridge, and all the best light. I\'ll take this as a consolation prize though. Beautiful evening at Fort Baker.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/gKEt89\n\n</div>\n</div>','Traffic Killed the Sunset','','publish','closed','open','','traffic-killed-the-sunset','','','2013-10-17 22:11:30','2013-10-18 04:11:30','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1170',0,'post','',0),(1172,1,'2013-10-18 19:47:34','2013-10-19 01:47:34','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2822/10354396505_ae2ebeaf6c.jpg\" />\n<div>\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/gLYZkF\n\n</div>\n</div>','Lake Tahoe Sunset','','publish','closed','open','','lake-tahoe-sunset','','','2013-10-18 19:47:34','2013-10-19 01:47:34','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1172',0,'post','',0),(1174,1,'2013-10-20 22:11:33','2013-10-21 04:11:33','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7372/10396352734_2902ab54a7_b.jpg\" />\n<div>Lonely walk in the rain.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/gQG2sW\n\n</div>\n</div>','Tokyo Rain','','publish','closed','open','','tokyo-rain','','','2013-10-20 22:11:33','2013-10-21 04:11:33','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1174',0,'post','',0),(1176,1,'2013-10-21 21:35:37','2013-10-22 03:35:37','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3686/10415195904_cc58a86809_b.jpg\" />\n<div>The nightly light show from looking out on Victoria Harbor &amp; Hong Kong island from Kowloon Peninsula.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/gSmATb\n\n</div>\n</div>','Everything But the Batsignal','','publish','closed','open','','everything-but-the-batsignal','','','2013-10-21 21:35:37','2013-10-22 03:35:37','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1176',0,'post','',0),(1178,1,'2013-10-22 12:54:04','2013-10-22 18:54:04','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3743/10426430516_0633b1a762.jpg\" />\n<div>\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/gTmbxo\n\n</div>\n</div>','Fog on the Bay Bridge. Rare.','','publish','closed','open','','fog-on-the-bay-bridge-rare','','','2013-10-22 12:54:04','2013-10-22 18:54:04','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1178',0,'post','',0),(1180,1,'2013-10-22 21:53:32','2013-10-23 03:53:32','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5481/10433345915_b9e2817b9d_b.jpg\" />\n<div>I was very fortunate to be back at One Market today when we looked out the window to see fog streaming over the Bay Bridge. Its a rare moment and I feel lucky to have been in the right place at the right time to catch this from this perspective.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/gTXCfp\n\n</div>\n</div>','Opportune Moments','','publish','closed','open','','opportune-moments','','','2013-10-22 21:53:32','2013-10-23 03:53:32','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1180',0,'post','',0),(1182,1,'2013-10-23 22:13:59','2013-10-24 04:13:59','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3683/10451931096_268a861b16_b.jpg\" />\n<div>This woman sat across from Melanie and I at a wine bar we went to in New Orleans. She was very pretty, obviously a waitress based on the converstaion she was having with the bartender, and apparantly led a, probably very fun, \"interesting\" life. She also had *bright* red hair. I\'m not a big fan of selective colorization, but sometimes it works well. This bar totally had atmosphere, and before I brought back in the Red, it was just missing something. This brought it all together.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/gVASYy\n\n</div>\n</div>','Red','','publish','closed','open','','red','','','2013-10-23 22:13:59','2013-10-24 04:13:59','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1182',0,'post','',0),(1184,1,'2013-10-24 22:47:21','2013-10-25 04:47:21','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3734/10469853983_afe8736263_b.jpg\" />\n<div>I shot this with my Tamron wide angle for my crop frame. Since I went to the D600 I haven\'t had a wide angle, but I just got in a 18-35mm f/3.5-4.5 and I\'m very excited to get out and shoot with it. So awesome to have a wide angle on my full frame!via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/gXbJPR\n\n</div>\n</div>','Wide Angle','','publish','closed','open','','wide-angle','','','2013-10-24 22:47:21','2013-10-25 04:47:21','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1184',0,'post','',0),(1186,1,'2013-10-28 17:24:45','2013-10-28 23:24:45','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7299/10545556333_9c2d455c0f.jpg\" />\n<div>\n\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/h4SJuM\n\n</div>\n</div>','New York, NY','','publish','closed','open','','new-york-ny','','','2013-10-28 17:24:45','2013-10-28 23:24:45','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1186',0,'post','',0),(1188,1,'2013-10-31 20:41:23','2013-11-01 02:41:23','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3794/10601932295_3147904d0f_b.jpg\" />\n<div>From some store in New Orleans, don\'t remember exactly which one.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/h9RF78\n\n</div>\n</div>','Happy Halloween!','','publish','closed','open','','happy-halloween','','','2013-10-31 20:41:23','2013-11-01 02:41:23','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1188',0,'post','',0),(1190,1,'2013-11-01 20:41:34','2013-11-02 02:41:34','<div><img style=\"max-width:600px;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7414/10619008905_d1d11f7992_b.jpg\" />\n<div>From the streets of Hong Kong.via Flickr http://flic.kr/p/hbncor\n\n</div>\n</div>','It&#039;s gotta move','','publish','closed','open','','its-gotta-move','','','2013-11-01 20:41:34','2013-11-02 02:41:34','',0,'http://clintsharp.com/?p=1190',0,'post','',0),(1219,1,'2013-11-02 18:47:42','2013-11-03 01:47:42','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3665/10636942803_c502cdee1d_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>Went out shooting with an empty camera. Whoops!<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/hcX7vz</div></div>','Remember that memory card?','','publish','closed','open','','remember-that-memory-card','','','2013-11-02 18:47:42','2013-11-03 01:47:42','',0,'http://clintsharp.wordpress.com/?p=1219',0,'post','',0),(1221,1,'2013-11-03 15:41:57','2013-11-03 23:41:57','<div><img src=\'http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5480/10658341435_ce20c981d1_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>I\'ve not participated previously in Selfy Sunday, but there\'s a first time for everything.  #selfysunday<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/heQMzv</div></div>','Selfy Sunday 1','','publish','closed','open','','selfy-sunday-1','','','2013-11-03 15:41:57','2013-11-03 23:41:57','',0,'http://clintsharp.wordpress.com/?p=1221',0,'post','',0),(1223,1,'2013-11-04 20:29:21','2013-11-05 04:29:21','<div><img src=\'http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5481/10683728255_162c7e76b8_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>I saw a picture by Swee Oh recently from a trip to the San Francisco zoo.  You can find it here: <a href=\"https://plus.google.com/102390118349128083852/posts/9WtZQmnnxBx\" rel=\"nofollow\">plus.google.com/102390118349128083852/posts/9WtZQmnnxBx</a> .  It was inspiring.  My family went to the Oakland zoo this weekend, and this is my much poorer imitation of the processing in that image.  Swee should really teach a class in how she processes, because I\'m really loving the B&amp;W images I\'m seeing from her recently.  Great job Swee!<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/hh5Uci</div></div>','Inspired','','publish','closed','open','','inspired','','','2013-11-04 20:29:21','2013-11-05 04:29:21','',0,'http://clintsharp.wordpress.com/?p=1223',0,'post','',0),(1225,1,'2013-11-05 20:29:22','2013-11-06 04:29:22','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3746/10702091663_b9f45914fa_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>I went to Lake Tahoe recently for the first time.  It was amazing.  I can\'t believe how big it is and I dong\'t think I\'ve ever seen a clearer lake.  I\'m looking forward to coming back in the winter.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/hiH1ZM</div></div>','First Times','','publish','closed','open','','first-times','','','2013-11-05 20:29:22','2013-11-06 04:29:22','',0,'http://clintsharp.wordpress.com/?p=1225',0,'post','',0),(1227,1,'2013-11-06 21:41:36','2013-11-07 05:41:36','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3810/10720145255_34bd372aa5_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>I\'ve been very unlucky this Fall.  I\'ve been out of town nearly every week or weekend day that had fog, and the ones that did I elected not to get up.  I\'ve had very bad luck.  This one view from Fort Baker is the only decent shot I\'ve gotten this season<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/hkixGB</div></div>','My Only Fog Shot','','publish','closed','open','','my-only-fog-shot','','','2013-11-06 21:41:36','2013-11-07 05:41:36','',0,'http://clintsharp.wordpress.com/?p=1227',0,'post','',0),(1229,1,'2013-11-07 19:53:29','2013-11-08 03:53:29','<div><img src=\'http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5503/10736235753_62ffa85070_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>Sometimes the shots you spend the least time preparing for are the best.  Taken after sunrise as I was walking back to my hotel.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/hmJ1QZ</div></div>','Snapshots','','publish','closed','open','','snapshots','','','2013-11-07 19:53:29','2013-11-08 03:53:29','',0,'http://clintsharp.wordpress.com/?p=1229',0,'post','',0),(1231,1,'2013-11-08 19:18:16','2013-11-09 03:18:16','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3675/10751858376_48b9625489_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>St. Louis Cathedral in New Orleans, LA.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/ho75Uy</div></div>','St. Louis Cathedral','','publish','closed','open','','st-louis-cathedral-2','','','2013-11-08 19:18:16','2013-11-09 03:18:16','',0,'http://clintsharp.wordpress.com/?p=1231',0,'post','',0),(1233,1,'2013-11-10 21:41:15','2013-11-11 05:41:15','<div><img src=\'http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5501/10793345625_692749e56e_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>I\'ve been waiting up earlier to catch the BART.  It\'s about twice as long as driving at its best time but its predictable, whereas driving is very stressful and variable.  It\'s also given me the excuse to walk about the city in the early mornings and take street photos.  This first morning doing that resulted in a few gems.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/hrLHBX</div></div>','A Better Commute','','publish','closed','open','','a-better-commute','','','2013-11-10 21:41:15','2013-11-11 05:41:15','',0,'http://clintsharp.wordpress.com/?p=1233',0,'post','',0),(1235,1,'2013-11-14 20:50:15','2013-11-15 04:50:15','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7446/10864558255_22f6680f46_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>From back in March.  It was very interesting weather that day, as I remember.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/hy4GDV</div></div>','Purple','','publish','closed','open','','purple','','','2013-11-14 20:50:15','2013-11-15 04:50:15','',0,'http://clintsharp.wordpress.com/?p=1235',0,'post','',0),(1237,1,'2013-11-15 19:35:27','2013-11-16 03:35:27','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7457/10879471503_0782fe6771_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>This was the first and only time I\'ve been out to shoot the Bay Lights.  Now that its getting dark earlier, I\'m guessing I\'ll get a few more shots from here as I walk home.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/hzo8QT</div></div>','Gold','','publish','closed','open','','gold','','','2013-11-15 19:35:27','2013-11-16 03:35:27','',0,'http://clintsharp.wordpress.com/?p=1237',0,'post','',0),(1239,1,'2013-11-16 19:53:36','2013-11-17 03:53:36','<div><img src=\'http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7302/10897060914_fbdc0539c6_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>I love big cats.  A relaxed picture for #caturday.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/hAWhyA</div></div>','Majestic','','publish','closed','open','','majestic','','','2013-11-16 19:53:36','2013-11-17 03:53:36','',0,'http://clintsharp.wordpress.com/?p=1239',0,'post','',0),(1241,1,'2013-11-17 22:17:41','2013-11-18 06:17:41','<div><img src=\'http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2841/10920570333_5fa9d91c36_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>Bought a cheap studio light set today and played around with how to be a strobist.  At the end of the day, I feel like I know a lot more.  Processed with Nik\'s Analog Efex Pro, which I am also digging.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/hD1M6p</div></div>','Learning Lighting','','publish','closed','open','','learning-lighting','','','2013-11-17 22:17:41','2013-11-18 06:17:41','',0,'http://clintsharp.wordpress.com/?p=1241',0,'post','',0),(1243,1,'2013-11-19 20:12:36','2013-11-20 04:12:36','<div><img src=\'http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2806/10955688986_e24ca17f02_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>I got lucky a couple of weeks back and finally caught some early morning fog.  I got up very early on a Friday on a hunch and made it over to the headlands.  Saw Max there as well.  Great morning.  More and more I\'m enjoying monochrome for my landscapes, and this fits well with my new penchant for B&amp;W.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/hG7LDq</div></div>','Finally, some fog!','','publish','closed','open','','finally-some-fog','','','2013-11-19 20:12:36','2013-11-20 04:12:36','',0,'http://clintsharp.wordpress.com/?p=1243',0,'post','',0),(1245,1,'2013-11-21 16:53:19','2013-11-22 00:53:19','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3758/10986563704_bc2d402429_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>About to head out to D&amp;C SF.  First time in months!  I\'m excited!  This is a view we\'re likely to see tonight, although without the sun :).<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/hJR1C9</div></div>','Welcome back Drink &amp; Click!','','publish','closed','open','','welcome-back-drink-click','','','2013-11-21 16:53:19','2013-11-22 00:53:19','',0,'http://clintsharp.wordpress.com/?p=1245',0,'post','',0),(1247,1,'2013-11-22 21:23:30','2013-11-23 05:23:30','<div><img src=\'http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3797/11004379945_f511839ee4_b.jpg\' style=\'max-width:600px;\' /><br /><div>I like fog in the early morning because capturing a long exposure is so much simpler than in the middle of the day.<br /><br />\nvia Flickr http://flic.kr/p/hLqjLH</div></div>','Rolling','','publish','closed','open','','rolling','','','2013-11-22 21:23:30','2013-11-23 05:23:30','',0,'http://clintsharp.wordpress.com/?p=1247',0,'post','',0),(1249,1